tive `Method.invoke(...)` call site.\n  - Temporarily sets `java.vendor` to an IBM-like value so Kafka’s static initialization reaches the `canLoad(...)` `Class.forName(...)` call site when the class is first initialized.\n\n- Updated `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/build.gradle`\n  - Adds required `--add-exports=java.security.jgss/sun.security.krb5=ALL-UNNAMED` for compilation, JVM tests, and native-image builds.\n  - Sets the JVM test `java.vendor` system property to help ensure the IBM-branch `canLoad(...)` path is exercised regardless of test ordering.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01c70654245d360c016a0f3f0cdb54819daa81e7cf7f3268f6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 610, "output": 1327, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36753, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779384055137, "responseId": "resp_01c70654245d360c016a0f3ef940e4819da66b6bc3653ddabf"}}
