[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class order and builds**\n\nI'm considering the test classes and whether the order is alphabetical after KafkaClients. It seems like OrgApache might follow Kafka? The build report's test order could be unpredictable depending on the classpath. I wonder if we can include specific entries in build.gradle.\n\nAlso, if a class initializes non-IBM, I can't reinitialize? I need to ensure that the global java.vendor is set to IBM before running all JVM tests. We've done this for the Test task, but I'm uncertain about native images. I might need to pass the vendor at build time.\n\n**Evaluating JVM properties**\n\nI'm thinking about the JVM agent and how the test `systemProperty` should be set before all tests. But I wonder if `systemProperty 'java.vendor'` can actually override the standard property. If it's in a forked JVM, could the command line option `-Djava.vendor` be ignored because the VM might overwrite it? I should check if running `java -Djava.vendor=IBM -XshowSettings` shows that Java allows this. It's all a bit tricky!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_01c70654245d360c016a0f40afaa64819da46532714e813269\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqD0C7JAbmS-XC2Mjo-n_IiCe1Ot2d5fpJvNS5UbMd0W9DtTi8unWrZ4uCnVgPRLLieWc8dtBVjVaW8yja0jBSrOLZy8aFbxoYiB8aTToj7BewdqNs9aW7ouufExHM83BS3KLnvYi3LbQ7342dGn4uM12vo4GN1O6Ko9S1DlhTe3z773lsssmSk0w6YjkdcChh99mSk3Le39w4geBtFoN7OhRp99IZ9-CbGyZ0YSocNsidrDceDtVuWL72AzUux7j9ic4z3j1U82BOLmvlWTnIblc6_1FltHUAXOw09YZa31gMsFo0OVSAtx6fM84CXjj47tzQFvchi_rNbHApttdd_BrRUfk4aUuBYQ9yUXlKnug_tWDxxW9TEMPRVIzMXJK-X4czFEptsuAzZIFHoW03L3RT6XETwdwwDUYP7f46Bk5ncFTVdQIF5eRc-iO9w_opgr3Wx3tV5D7ceygTCbh-DjULDjRAmj5AMtPDOiUE155e-J8Lp5L-H1j78K3PvioipPIIfmqzFeDIBL_zCqLOX0ykLJsvhb21inBIjLWEgvmlov737lYxJW_MpQgsIW-jHdcqJxyWRRa9n4Pmnb5YexeyoGrRoq6C9IqmRsnclqfFS1PZxQnANYLHL0YOWWEUPw2u8Sgz8kDeE2lKcIRP51pUBBbNL0HvmYtn9QeTmyjvK47dtSEjPJk