eption occurs instead of an error, is that acceptable? So, I could avoid dynamic loading in native by using a try-catch pattern for unsupported operations.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xxGM7mPfYYAlcPQqgJryi6Hy|fc_01c70654245d360c016a0f411986a8819d972b97f57f46c9d3", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/OrgApacheKafkaCommonSecurityKerberosKerberosErrorTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    private String childFirstClasspath() {\n        return serviceRoot + File.pathSeparator + System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n    }\n", "newText": "    private String childFirstClasspath() {\n        return serviceRoot + File.pathSeparator + System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\", \"\");\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 993, "output": 1031, "cacheRead": 52224, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54248, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779384586221, "responseId": "resp_01c70654245d360c016a0f410ad890819d896d8b8a4668b3d4"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_xxGM7mPfYYAlcPQqgJryi6Hy|fc_01c70654245d360c016a0f411986a8819d972b97f57f46c9d3", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/OrgApacheKafkaCommonSecurityKerberosKerberosErrorTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n 84         }\n 85     }\n 86 \n 87     private String childFirstClasspath() {\n-88         return serviceRoot + File.pathSeparator + System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n+88         return serviceRoot + File.pathSeparator + System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\", \"\");\n 89     }\n 90 \n 91     private static void restoreJavaVendor(String previousVendor) {\n 92         if (previousVendor =