 is acceptable, as the current instruction supports it. Returning after the catch aligns with existing code. I need to check how runtime classpath in the native build interacts with initialization; this could lead to issues if classes are already initialized. I’ll also think about how Class.forName failures are counted.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dynamic access reports**\\n\\nI need to ensure the process is successful. I'm considering whether the dynamic-access report for `Class.forName` relies on call site execution, even if it's unsuccessful. The report likely lists uncovered dynamic access call sites after static analysis, focusing on successful `Method.invoke` calls. If a `Class.forName` call fails due to a missing class, it might not generate reachability metadata. I suspect the report on \\\"Remaining uncovered call sites\\\" comes from JaCoCo instrumentation analyzing class coverage.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined the active `KerberosError` test to force a fresh initialization path that reaches `KerberosError.canLoad(...)`.\n\nUpdated:\n\n- `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/OrgApacheKafkaCommonSecurityKerberosKerberosErrorTest.java`\n  - Added a child-first classloader based test.\n  - Sets `java.vendor` to an IBM-like value before loading a fresh copy of Kafka’s `KerberosError`.\n  - Uses `ServiceLoader` and a nested `Runnable` helper to invoke the public `KerberosError.fromException(...)` path without direct test reflection.\n  - Catches only Native Image unsupported dynamic-class-loading `Error`s via `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(...)`.\n\n- `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/build.gradle`\n  - Added native runtime `java.class.path` so the dynamic class-loading path can resolve test/runtime classes when applicable.\n\nThis should avoid the previous issue where the system-loaded `KerberosError` was already initialized before the test